title: Red Foley - Tennessee Saturday Night - 2 CDs (320)
description:
Red Foley - Tennessee Saturday Night - 2 CD (320)

Red Foley was an old time country singer who became popular during the post-war era and performed extensively through the mid sixties.  His hits include "Smoke on the Water" in 1944, "New Jolie Blonde" in 1947, "Tennessee Saturday Night" in 1948, and "Chattanoogie Shoe Shine Boy" in 1950, which came to be his signature song.  In later years, Red Foley would dabble in rockabilly, R&B, and gospel music.
